         <gmd:abstract>
            <gco:CharacterString>These data were collected by the Joint Airborne Lidar Bathymetry Technical Center of Expertise using the CHARTS system.
The data includes hydrographic and topographic data.  This data was collected Post-Hurricane Ivan in Alabama and Florida.
      
Original contact information: 
   Contact Org: NOAA Office for Coastal Management
   Phone: 843-740-1202
   Email: coastal.info@noaa.gov
This data set has 3639.0 columns and 3188.0.The data set was generated from a larger data set and includes all valid data within the requested geographic bounds.
    </gco:CharacterString>
         </gmd:abstract>
         <gmd:purpose>
            <gco:CharacterString>The data were collected to depict the elevations above and below water along the immediate coastal zone.</gco:CharacterString>
         </gmd:purpose>
         <gmd:credit>
            <gco:CharacterString>Acknowledgement of the Joint Airborne Lidar Bathymetry Center of Expertise (JALBTCX) would be appreciated in
any publications or derived products.</gco:CharacterString>
         </gmd:credit>
